As of June 2011, we expect GHC 7 and cabal-install >= 0.10.2.  Use a recent
cabal-dev as well (something like 0.7.4.x on Cabal 1.10.x).

Follow the instructions below with <repo root>/Java as your current
directory.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To use the ABC backend (recommended):

(NB: "make" should just work for you if you clone the abcBridge repo
into the parent directory of the Verifier repo root.)

1. Check out the abcBridge repo.
1. Check out the jvm-parser repo.
2. $ cabal-dev install . ../Verinf <abcBridge location> <jvm-parser location>

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To DISABLE the ABC backend (uses the Aiger package):

1. Check out the Aiger repo.
2. $ cabal-dev install . ../Verinf <Aiger location> <jvm-parser location> --flags=-abc-backend
